article.headline: UMBC 80, Hartford 63
article.story: WEST HARTFORD, Conn. -- Jay Greene scored 22 points and Darryl Proctor added 20 as Maryland-Baltimore County beat Hartford 80-63 on Saturday. Hartford (6-21, 2-11 America East) trailed by four at the half, but UMBC outscored the Hawks 16-5 over the opening 5:20 of the second half. Once UMBC (12-13, 6-7) pushed its lead into double digits, the Hawks never got closer than nine points the rest of the way. Chauncey Gilliam finished with 18 points while Matt Spadafora added 11 for UMBC. David Bookman paced Hartford with a career-high 17 points. Jaret von Rosenberg and Clayton Brothers each finished with 12 points for the Hawks, while Michael Turner contributed 11 points.
